cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and sequence-to-sequence models. The paper proposes a new dataset called NACS, which requires mapping actions back to the original commands, and shows that it exhibits properties more closely aligned with realistic use-cases for sequence-to-sequence models. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are closely related to natural language processing and sequence-to-sequence models. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the SCAN dataset and proposes a complementary dataset, which may also make it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
